Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "baba" in different forms and positions:

1. *Baba* me je naučila da pravim pite. (My *grandmother* taught me how to make pies.)
2. Volim da odem kod *babe* na selo. (I love going to the countryside to visit my *grandmother*.)
3. *Babi* je teško da hoda zbog problema sa kolenom. (My *grandmother* has trouble walking due to knee problems.)
4. Sinoć sam sanjala svoju pokojnu *babu*. (Last night I dreamt of my deceased *grandmother*.)
5. *Babama* je drago kad dođemo u posetu. (Our *grandmothers* are happy when we come to visit.)
6. *Babe* su često brižne i pažljive prema svojim unucima. (Grandmothers are often caring and attentive towards their grandchildren.)
7. Kad sam bila mala, *baba* mi je često pričala priče o princezama i vilenjacima. (When I was little, my *grandmother* often told me stories about princesses and fairies.)
8. Moja *baba* je najbolja kada pravi domaći hleb. (My *grandmother* is the best at making homemade bread.)

Note: The word "baba" can mean "grandmother" or "old woman" depending on the context.